      "conditioning_notes": "`<CHAR_A>`'s love of feeling everything loudly and fear of being dismissed surface in the hallway non-laugh spiral — they're reading a pause like a verdict and immediately perform self-awareness about it. The home location keeps this grounded and low-temperature: the anxiety reads as genuine without requiring real stakes, because domestic familiarity makes small social moments feel both safe and weirdly high-pressure. `<CHAR_B>`'s Compass core shows up in how they hold the space between `<CHAR_A>` and `<CHAR_C>` — not attached to outcomes, observant enough to find the angle that moves things forward (\"the crack is giving character\"). `<CHAR_C>`'s fear of the thing not being good drives the broken-prop beat — it's not the break itself that stings, it's that the work was mid-process and therefore still vulnerable. The strangers-to-friends arc between `<CHAR_A>` and `<CHAR_B>` progresses through friction (the laugh beat) into genuine warmth (the \"you're smiling\" closer) without a dramatic declaration — they just stop being careful around each other. The nano LM should learn that home-location arcs don't need external threat; the domestic setting lets character self-consciousness carry the tension."
